## ⚙️ Local setup

### Backend

```bash
cd backend
python -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
uvicorn app.main:app --reload --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000
```

 **environment variables that must be very very included**:

```bash
ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
# ======================

# FastAPI Config
DEBUG=True
APP_NAME=ShieldLabs
APP_VERSION=1.0.0
ENVIRONMENT=development

# Database
DATABASE_URL=sqlite:///./shieldlabs.db

# Groq API (get from console.groq.com)
GROQ_API_KEY=" i used the groq api key because i didnt have other choice , i didnt had acess to the gpt api key, so for the sever reasoning i used this model and cvss score and heavy resoning only , if i had acess for the gpt api key i would blindly use the gpt api model "

# Ollama Config (local LLM)
OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434
OLLAMA_MODEL=qwen2.5-coder:7b

# GitHub (for cloning repos)
GITHUB_TOKEN="this one is for the auto pr feature , its not necessary for you to upload cause when u use auto pr feature u need to enter github ssh token manually , and it isnt stored by this project because its critical "

# Security
SECRET_KEY=" cant publish my security here "

# Logging
LOG_LEVEL=INFO
LOG_FILE=logs/shieldlabs.log

# Scanning Config
SCAN_TIMEOUT=600  # 10 minutes
NMAP_TIMEOUT=60   # 1 minute
SQLMAP_TIMEOUT=30 # 30 seconds

# API Rate Limiting
MAX_REQUESTS_PER_DAY=150  # Groq free tier limit
REQUESTS_PER_SECOND=2

# File Upload
MAX_UPLOAD_SIZE=104857600  # 100MB
ALLOWED_EXTENSIONS=.zip,.py,.js,.go,.java,.rb

# Paths
TEMP_DIR=./temp
LOGS_DIR=./logs
REPORTS_DIR=./reports
"this were my path your might be diff or could be same "


NUCLEI_PATH=" your path " Important think , nuclie often gets blocked by windows whn u download and tries to run so makre sure that when u install , installation happened properly with no enviroment variable conflict and local window security conflict 

# ========================
# SCAN MODE CONFIGURATION
# ========================

# PASSIVE = safe recon only (default, no exploitation)
# ACTIVE  = includes sqlmap SQLi testing (requires explicit user consent per scan)
DEFAULT_SCAN_MODE=passive

# sqlmap path (required only for active mode)
# Find with: where.exe sqlmap OR check pip show sqlmap


# Active scan safety: max requests sqlmap sends per target (prevents abuse)
SQLMAP_MAX_REQUESTS=50

# Reminder message shown to user before active scan starts
ACTIVE_SCAN_CONSENT_MESSAGE=Active scanning tests for vulnerabilities using real attack payloads. Only use on systems you own or have explicit written permission to test. Unauthorized scanning may be illegal.

# SQLMap - use official repo, not pip install (Windows Smart App Control bypass)
SQLMAP_PATH="your path "

SQLMAP_PYTHON="your path "
```

### Frontend

```bash
cd frontend
npm install
npm run dev
```

The Vite dev server runs on port `3000` and proxies `/api` requests to `http://localhost:8000`.

